Method summary
Build a TF-IDF representation from concatenated product fields (title, description, category, material, origin_district).

For each query, compute cosine similarity against all product vectors.

Apply a local boost (multiplicative factor) to products whose origin_district is in Rwanda.

Add a small popularity prior from click counts.

If the top global match is non-local and no local item passes the similarity threshold, trigger a curated fallback that filters local products by category/material keywords.

